# Fishmarket v3 – Routes

All routes live under `src/app/` using the Next.js App Router. Update this file whenever routes are added, removed, or restructured.

## `ROUTES` constant

All route paths are defined in **`src/lib/routes.ts`** as the `ROUTES` object. Always import from there instead of hardcoding path strings:

```ts
import { ROUTES } from "@/lib/routes";

router.push(ROUTES.createListing);        // "/create-listing"
router.push(ROUTES.editListing("abc123")); // "/create-listing/abc123/edit"
<Link href={ROUTES.home}>Home</Link>      // "/"
```

When adding a new route, add its path to `ROUTES` first, then reference the key everywhere.

## Route protection

Protected routes require authentication. Unauthenticated users are redirected to `/login`.

- **`AuthProvider`** (`src/contexts/AuthContext.tsx`) wraps the app in the root layout, providing `{ user, loading }` via context.
- **`useAuth`** (`src/hooks/useAuth.ts`) is a re-export of `useAuthContext` — use it in any client component.
- **`ProtectedRoute`** (`src/components/ProtectedRoute/`) is a wrapper component that checks auth and redirects to `/login` if not authenticated. Shows a loading spinner while auth state resolves.
- To protect a route group, add a `layout.tsx` that wraps children with `<ProtectedRoute>` (see `src/app/create-listing/layout.tsx`).

